snippet.textDisplay:
One fun fact that does not get mentioned: Abraham Lincoln had correspondence with Karl Marx. The President of the U.S was friends with one of the most cited authors in history (i believe the 17th most cited author)

I'm not making this up by the way, Karl Marx inspired Abraham Lincoln decision to end slavery and congratulated him on his re-election as well! So the idea that he was just ''preserving the union'' was simply Abraham Lincoln being clever and trying to convince as many people to support the war I.E Rhetoric!
